  "faq": {
    "title": "Frequently Asked Questions",
    "subtitle": "Got questions? We've got answers. If you don't find what you're looking for, feel free to contact our support team.",
    "items": [
      {
        "question": "How do I choose the right fabric?",
        "answer": "Consider the room's function: linen and cotton are great for living spaces due to their breathability, while velvet adds luxury to bedrooms. For high sun exposure, choose fade-resistant fabrics. Order free swatches to see colors in your actual lighting."
      },
      {
        "question": "What sizes do you offer?",
        "answer": "All our curtains are custom-made to your exact measurements. We can accommodate widths from 20\" to 300\" and lengths from 24\" to 144\". Simply enter your dimensions during checkout, and we'll craft the perfect fit."
      },
      {
        "question": "How do I care for my curtains?",
        "answer": "Most fabrics can be dry cleaned. Linen and cotton may be machine washed on gentle cycle in cold water. Always check the care label. Regular vacuuming with a brush attachment helps maintain freshness."
      },
      {
        "question": "What's your delivery timeline?",
        "answer": "Each order is handcrafted and takes 7-10 business days to produce. Shipping takes an additional 3-5 business days. You'll receive tracking information as soon as your order ships. Rush production available for a fee."
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I return or exchange?",
        "answer": "Since all items are custom-made to your specifications, we cannot accept returns. However, if there's a manufacturing defect, contact us within 30 days for a free replacement. We recommend ordering swatches first."
      },
      {
        "question": "Do you offer installation?",
        "answer": "We provide detailed DIY installation guides and video tutorials. Installation is straightforward with basic tools. For complex projects, we can recommend local installers in select metropolitan areas."
      }
    ]
  },
